        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 4:09PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Neola, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts up to 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Loose objects may be knocked over due to gusty winds.

Locations impacted include...
Neola...
Hot Springs...
Lake Moomaw...
Ingalls Field...
Carloover...
Bacova Junction...
and Natural Well.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
